---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const post = {
  title: 'Building a Modern Personal Website with Astro',
  date: '2025-10-23',
  readTime: '5 min read',
  tags: ['Astro', 'Web Development', 'JavaScript'],
  author: 'Chunjie Liu',
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} - Chunjie Liu`}
  description="Learn how to build a modern personal website using Astro's static site generation"
>
  <div class='container'>
    <article class='blog-post fade-in-up'>
      <header class='post-header card'>
        <div class='post-meta'>
          <time class='post-date'
            >{
              new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
                year: 'numeric',
                month: 'long',
                day: 'numeric',
              })
            }</time
          >
          <span class='post-read-time'>{post.readTime}</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class='post-title'>{post.title}</h1>

        <div class='post-tags'>
          {post.tags.map((tag) => <span class='tag'>{tag}</span>)}
        </div>

        <div class='author-info'>
          <span>By {post.author}</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class='post-content card'>
        <p>
          When I decided to rebuild my personal website, I wanted something that
          was fast, modern, and easy to maintain. After exploring various
          options, I chose Astro for its unique approach to static site
          generation and its excellent developer experience.
        </p>

        <h2>Why Astro?</h2>
        <p>
          Astro stands out from other static site generators for several
          reasons:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Zero JavaScript by default:</strong> Astro ships zero JavaScript
            to the client by default, making sites incredibly fast.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Component Islands:</strong> You can add interactive components
            only where needed, keeping the rest of your site static.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Framework agnostic:</strong> Use React, Vue, Svelte, or any other
            framework components within the same project.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Developer experience:</strong> Great tooling, TypeScript support,
            and intuitive file-based routing.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <p>
          Setting up an Astro project is straightforward. You can start with
          their CLI tool:
        </p>
        <pre><code>npm create astro@latest my-website</code></pre>
        <p>
          This will scaffold a new Astro project with everything you need to get
          started.
        </p>

        <h2>Project Structure</h2>
        <p>A typical Astro project has a clean, intuitive structure:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <code>src/pages/</code> - Your website pages (supports .astro, .md, .js
            files)
          </li>
          <li><code>src/layouts/</code> - Reusable layout components</li>
          <li><code>src/components/</code> - UI components</li>
          <li><code>public/</code> - Static assets</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Key Features I Used</h2>
        <p>For this website, I leveraged several Astro features:</p>

        <h3>Layout Components</h3>
        <p>
          I created a base layout that includes the navigation, footer, and
          common meta tags. This ensures consistency across all pages while
          keeping the code DRY.
        </p>

        <h3>Static Site Generation</h3>
        <p>
          All pages are pre-rendered at build time, resulting in lightning-fast
          loading speeds and excellent SEO performance.
        </p>

        <h3>TypeScript Support</h3>
        <p>
          Astro has excellent TypeScript support out of the box, which helps
          catch errors early and improves the development experience.
        </p>

        <h2>Performance Benefits</h2>
        <p>
          The performance benefits of using Astro are immediately noticeable:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Near-instant page loads due to pre-rendered HTML</li>
          <li>Minimal JavaScript bundle sizes</li>
          <li>Excellent Core Web Vitals scores</li>
          <li>SEO-friendly static HTML</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>
          Building this website with Astro has been a great experience. The
          framework strikes an excellent balance between simplicity and power,
          making it perfect for personal websites, blogs, and even more complex
          projects.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you're considering building a new website or rebuilding an existing
          one, I highly recommend giving Astro a try. Its focus on performance,
          developer experience, and flexibility makes it a compelling choice for
          modern web development.
        </p>
      </div>

      <footer class='post-footer card'>
        <div class='post-navigation'>
          <a href='/blog' class='nav-link'>‚Üê Back to Blog</a>
          <div class='share-buttons'>
            <span>Share this post:</span>
            <a href='#' class='share-button'>Twitter</a>
            <a href='#' class='share-button'>LinkedIn</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

